This lets people combine the different state ingredient types into a single ingredient.
Example:
```json
{
  "type": "botania:pure_daisy",
  "input": {
    "type": "compound",
    "ingredients": [
      {
        "type": "block",
        "block": "minecraft:stone"
      },
      {
        "type": "tag",
        "tag": "minecraft:wool"
      }
    ]
  },
  "output": {
    "name": "botania:livingrock"
  }
}
```

The main reason I added it was because it will be needed for the upcoming CraftTweaker support PR.

This PR adds support for adding dynamic mana infusion recipes, i.e. recipes whose outputs depend on their inputs, for both CraftTweaker and API users.

Example:
Enchanted mana helment infusion recipe which transfers NBT.
![before](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/11538216/107164030-dd1ab480-69a4-11eb-884c-7f25980fabf9.png)
![after](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/11538216/107164032-ddb34b00-69a4-11eb-9a57-d6d7b1228769.png)
With the script:
```zs
import crafttweaker.api.item.IItemStack;

val copyNbt = (output as IItemStack, input as IItemStack) => { return output.withTag(input.tag); };

<recipetype:botania:mana_infusion>.addRecipe("mana_infusion_helmet", <item:botania:manasteel_helmet>, <item:minecraft:iron_helmet>.anyDamage(), 500, null, copyNbt);
<recipetype:botania:mana_infusion>.addRecipe("mana_infusion_chestplate", <item:botania:manasteel_chestplate>, <item:minecraft:iron_chestplate>.anyDamage(), 800, null, copyNbt);
<recipetype:botania:mana_infusion>.addRecipe("mana_infusion_leggings", <item:botania:manasteel_leggings>, <item:minecraft:iron_leggings>.anyDamage(), 700, null, copyNbt);
<recipetype:botania:mana_infusion>.addRecipe("mana_infusion_boots", <item:botania:manasteel_boots>, <item:minecraft:iron_boots>.anyDamage(), 400, null, copyNbt);
```

Adds CraftTweaker support for nearly all recipe types, only one missing is brews, which I may PR at a later stage.

Docs will be PR'd to the CraftTweaker Docs repo, and will be hosted on https://docs.blamejared.com

This is the script I used to test it, it should cover everything that can be done in JSON with it


Also I put CraftTweaker has a compileOnly because we don't really have an `:api` and I don't think you guys really want waste the CPU cycles loading more mods when deving, happy to change it though

